d <- readMat("StopSearchData.mat")

m <- d$m # 83  x 9  
p <- d$p # 30 x 2  
v <- as.numeric(d$v) # 9  validity
x <- as.numeric(d$x)
y <- d$y # 20 x 30 

n <- dim(m)[1] #  83
nc <- dim(m)[2] #  9
nq <- dim(p)[1] #  30
ns <- dim(y)[1] #  20

3 MCMC

data <- list("y", "m", "p", "v", "nc", "nq", "ns")

# parameters to be monitored:
parameters <- c('gamma', 'ypred')

# model
model_text <- "
# Take The Best
model{   
  # Data
  for (q in 1:nq){
    for (i in 1:ns){
      y[i,q] ~ dbern(ttb[t[q]])
      ypred[i,q] ~ dbern(ttb[t[q]])
    }
  }
  # TTB Model For Each Question
  for (q in 1:nq){  
    # Add Cue Contributions To Mimic TTB Decision
    for (j in 1:nc){
      tmp1[q,j] <- (m[p[q,1],j]-m[p[q,2],j])*pow(2,s[j]-1) 
    } 
    # Find if Cue Favors First, Second, or Neither Stimulus
    tmp2[q] <- sum(tmp1[q,1:nc]) # A    , B    . A B  0.
    tmp3[q] <- -1*step(-tmp2[q])+step(tmp2[q]) # A -> 1, B -> -1, or 0
    t[q] <- tmp3[q]+2 # A -> 3, B-> 1, or 2
  }
  # Cue Search Order Follows Validities
  s[1:nc] <- rank(v[1:nc])
  # Choose TTB Decision With Probability Gamma, or Guess
  ttb[1] <- 1-gamma
  ttb[2] <- 0.5
  ttb[3] <- gamma
  # Priors
  gamma ~ dunif(0.5,1)
}
"

samples <- jags(data, parameters.to.save = parameters, 
                model.file = textConnection(model_text), 
                n.chains=1, n.iter=5000, n.burnin=2000, n.thin=1)
